casebody.data:
Toledo Bar Association v. Carrigan.

[Cite as Toledo Bar Assn. v. Carrigan (1994), 71 Ohio St.3d 256.]

(No. 93-2536 Submitted November 2, 1994 Decided December 20, 1994.) *257George Gemot III and David F. Cooper, for relator. *258William, M. Connelly and Steven R. Smith, for respondent. Per Curiam.

Based upon our review, the findings and recommendations of the board are affirmed. Respondent is hereby publicly reprimanded and costs are taxed to him.

Judgment accordingly.

Moyer, C.J., A.W. Sweeney, Douglas, Wright, Resnick and F.E. Sweeney, JJ., concur. Pfeifer, J., dissents and would dismiss the cause.
